==English==

===Noun===
'''cat<nowiki>'</nowiki>s-paw''' (''plural'' '''cat's-paws''' or '''cats'-paws'''); also '''catspaw''' (''plural'' '''catspaws''')

====Meaning ''pawn''====
A [[pawn]] or [[dupe]]; somebody who has been unwittingly tricked into acting in another's interest. From a [[fable]], perhaps of [[Wikipedia:Aesop|Aesop]]'s, in which a crafty monkey begs a cat to pull hot [[chestnut]]s from a fire. The cat singes his paw, and the monkey gobbles up the chestnuts leaving none for the cat.

====Meaning ''knot''====
A kind of [[knot]] resembling a [[lark's-foot]] hitch; see [[Wikipedia:cat's paw (knot)]] for more detailed information.

